the charge in shaping a values-based response. With a focus on the power of education, Mulligan proposes that the solutions to workforce upheaval lie in reskilling and retraining for individuals and companies adapting to rapid change. By creating lifelong learning opportunities that break down boundaries between the classroom and the workplace, businesses can foster personal and career well-being and growth for their employees. Drawing on her own experiences, historical examples, and reports from the frontiers where these issues are unfolding, Mulligan details how business leaders can prepare for and respond to technological disruption. Providing a framework for concrete and meaningful action, Hire Purpose is an essential read about the transformations that will shape the next decade and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAutomationxEconomic aspects. 0aBusiness. 0aEmployeesxEffect of automation on. 0aSocial responsibility of business. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh1 aAuguste, Byron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaw, Greg, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311071097708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/mull1794840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231553124423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isb